data.text: @ThatAgnes And you should have been somewhere living an actual life.
@mila_marshallt @TophHooperton Probably because she's asked questions about it by other contestants/production staff who need something juicy for the confessionals.
@ThatAgnes She identified as Celine Dion. Therefore she was Celine Dion.

@mila_marshallt @TophHooperton I've seen her do better looks, and her runway wasn't my kind of thing. But I don't get the bitter Bob thing; I thunk she's honest and smart and it's amplified by shady editing.
@mila_marshallt @ThatAgnes If an upturned papier mache volcano is iconic then I guess she was?
@teriwolfpants I didn't mind her first time round but she's not doing herself many favours this time, even if you take dodgy editing into account.
@ThatAgnes I thought she did excellent Stevie makeup and if the other stuff is true that’s really rough. I think Kennedy should have gone either way.

@TophHooperton Apparently she asked for a broom but they wouldn't let her, whereas BDLC got a bag etc. And she was basically told to twirl a bit but others got actual choreography designed to be funny. And she looked more like her diva than Milk. Her runway was hideous though.

@ThatAgnes It’s true that some of the parts were inherently funny and some lame which was totally out of their control. I think Aja is right that she could have had more fun playing up the witchyness though and her runway was a disaster
@TophHooperton Shamefully I don't know a single thing about Patti LaB so I couldn't possibly comment. But Thorgy was totally set up and didn't deserve to go. I felt bad for her.
@ThatAgnes These are my exact thoughts too. Chi chi channelled Miss Patti so exquisitely I thought she could have been top 3.
